{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":201324,"duration_api_ms":199444,"num_turns":14,"result":"I've explored the project thoroughly. Here's what I found:\n\n**Already exists:**\n- `ListaEspera` model with `id, alumno_id, turno_id, posicion, fecha` + unique constraint\n- `ListaEsperaCreate` and `ListaEsperaRead` Pydantic schemas\n- Waitlist helpers in `inscripcion_service.py`: `_next_waitlist_position`, `_promote_from_waitlist`, `_recalculate_waitlist_positions`\n\n**Missing (what we need to build):**\n- `app/api/lista_espera.py` — the router (no endpoint exists yet)\n- `app/services/lista_espera_service.py` — dedicated service layer\n- Registration in `main.py`\n- Tests\n\nThe design space is narrow since the model, schemas, and helper logic are already in place. Before I propose the full design, one clarification:\n\n**Should the POST endpoint for adding to the waitlist go through the same validation as enrollment (active membership, plan limits, etc.)?** The existing flow in `inscripcion_service.inscribir_alumno()` automatically adds to the waitlist when there's no cupo. The task asks for a separate `POST /api/lista-espera` — should this:\n\n**(A)** Be a direct waitlist add that only validates the student/turno exist and the turno is full (simpler, for admin/receptionist use)?\n**(B)** Go through full enrollment validation (membership, plan limits) — essentially a dedicated entry point that always targets the waitlist?\n\nMy recommendation is **(B)** — reuse existing validation so we don't create a backdoor that bypasses membership checks. The POST endpoint would validate the same way, but always add to waitlist (with appropriate position assignment). What do you think?","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"26d46607-a830-486d-bea3-7a832e869277","total_cost_usd":0.6401427,"usage":{"input_tokens":15,"cache_creation_input_tokens":39089,"cache_read_input_tokens":273865,"output_tokens":3176,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web